<body>

   
    <div class="recipe-container">
        <h1>Authentic Mutton Biryani Recipe</h1>
        

        <h2>Ingredients:</h2>
        <ul class="ingredients-list">
            <li>500g Mutton (Goat Meat)</li>
            <li>2 cups Basmati Rice</li>
            <li>2 tbsp Ghee or Oil</li>
            <li>1 Bay Leaf</li>
            <li>2 Cloves</li>
            <li>1-inch Cinnamon Stick</li>
            <li>2 Cardamoms</li>
            <li>1 Large Onion (sliced)</li>
            <li>1 Tomato (chopped)</li>
            <li>1 tbsp Ginger-Garlic Paste</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Yogurt</li>
            <li>1 tsp Turmeric Powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp Red Chili Powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp Coriander Powder</li>
            <li>1 tsp Garam Masala</li>
            <li>1 tsp Cumin Seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Mint Leaves</li>
            <li>1/2 cup Coriander Leaves</li>
            <li>4 cups Water</li>
            <li>Salt to taste</li>
            <li>Saffron Strands (optional)</li>
            <li>1/4 cup Warm Milk</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Instructions:</h2>
        <ol class="instructions-list">
            <li>Wash and soak basmati rice for 30 minutes.</li>
            <li>Marinate mutton with yogurt, turmeric, chili powder, salt, and garam masala for 1 hour.</li>
            <li>Heat ghee in a large pan and add bay leaf, cloves, cinnamon, and cardamom.</li>
            <li>Add cumin seeds, sliced onions, and sauté until golden brown.</li>
            <li>Add ginger-garlic paste and sauté until fragrant.</li>
            <li>Add chopped tomatoes, coriander powder, and cook until soft.</li>
            <li>Add marinated mutton and cook for 10 minutes.</li>
            <li>Add water, cover, and cook for 30-40 minutes until mutton is tender.</li>
            <li>In another pot, cook the soaked rice until 70% done, then drain.</li>
            <li>Layer the mutton with rice, sprinkle saffron milk, mint, and coriander leaves.</li>
            <li>Cover and cook on low flame (Dum method) for 15-20 minutes.</li>
            <li>Fluff the biryani gently and serve hot with raita or salan.</li>
        </ol>
    </div>

</body>
